Path: godot/tutorials/navigation/navigation_using_navigationservers.rst
Summary: This section explains how to communicate with the NavigationServer using RIDs to reference internal objects.
To work with the NavigationServer means to prepare parameters for a query that can be sent to the NavigationServer for updates or requesting data. To reference the internal NavigationServer objects like maps, regions and agents RIDs are used as identification numbers. Every navigation related node in the scene tree has a function that returns the RID for this node.
