Path: godot/tutorials/navigation/navigation_using_navigationservers.rst
Summary: This section details the functional equivalence and potential cross-dimensional usage of NavigationServer2D and NavigationServer3D.
NavigationServer2D and NavigationServer3D are equivalent in functionality for their dimension.

It is technically possible to use the tools for creating navigation meshes in one dimension for the other dimension. For example, baking a 2D navigation mesh with the 3D NavigationMesh when using flat 3D source geometry, or creating 3D flat navigation meshes with the polygon outline draw tools of NavigationRegion2D and NavigationPolygons.
